snippet.textDisplay: This song really hit home for me when I heard it and saw the video. Recently I lost a close friend to Heroin and it came as such a shock to me. I have been struggling with a Methamphetamine addiction for six years now and I've been six months clean and when he passed in October of last year it broke me. I miss him so much and wish he was still here, I feel guilt that I am here and he is not sometimes. But this song reminds me of him so much and it reminds me of where I was and I'm glad I found my way out of that just wish my friend could have as well. I want to believe he is in a better place now, hopefully free of pain.
